text.tspan: Real-time, interactive single-cell simulations in WebGPU.

tspan.tspan: Design principles and benefits of WebGPU:
interactive simulations and computational art in the scientific process
active filaments in a self-generating potential

text.tspan: Eligibility: Students and Researchers at Kyoto University

tspan.tspan: Grisha Szep will present about real-time, interactive single-cell
simulations in WebGPU, where active filaments self-organize into
motile cytoskeletal structures. He will also introduce WebGPU and
its potential for scalable, browser-based scientific simulations and
computational art, connecting artificial life, microbial evolution,
and open-ended exploration of emergent cellular behaviors.
